http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/2217-get-placements/article14596318.ece

Scores of people received placement offers at a job fair organised by the Ministry of Labour and Employment and Society for Integrated Growth of the Nation here on Sunday.60 companiesNearly 60 companies participated in the fair held at St. Albert’s Higher Secondary School here. About 5,000 offers were made and 2,217 persons got placements, said a pressnote. C. K. Menon, industrialist, inaugurated the programme. A.N. Radhakrishnan, chairman, Make in Kerala, presided over the function. He said that similar job fairs would be held in other districts.